# GUID

Any request to the API must be done by
providing a valid token plus your api key. The token can be retrieved through an authentication request.
The authentication request itself must be done by providing a valid API key.

## Authentication [/authenticate]

### Authenticate [GET]
When successfully authenticated, you are given a token which is valid for a maximum of 1 day.

+ Request (application/json)

    + Headers

            x-api-key: api_key_value

+ Response 200 (application/json)

        {
            "status": "authenticated",
            "value": "0251791b002f142fe7524f5770b63f78d6a719471a690a17955e31df7fe333db",
            "expires": "2018-03-27 08:57:09"
        }

## GUIDS Object [/guids/{guid}]

+ Parameters
    + guid (string) - GUID value

### Get GUID object [GET]
Retrieve information about a guid object

+ Request (application/json)

    + Headers

            x-api-key: api_key_value
            x-token: token_value

+ Response 200 (application/json)

        {
            "data": {
                "guid": "e0f1b2c8-d48f-4141-be90-cd05679083e6",
                "status": "assigned",
                "assigned_to": "EMMA",
                "created_at": "2018-03-26 09:09:20",
                "assigned_at": "2018-03-27 10:19:25"
            }
        }

## GUIDS Collection [/guids]

